{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/eng/Operations/24-06-22/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<blockquote>\n<p>This post documents how to receive events via AWS Lambda and AWS SQS, and send alert notifications to Slack for specific events. Lambda development was done using the AWS Toolkit for VSCode, and Slack notifications were implemented using a Slack webhook bot.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"aws-serverless-application-model-sam\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#aws-serverless-application-model-sam\" aria-label=\"aws serverless application model sam permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>AWS Serverless Application Model (SAM)</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Install AWS SAM CLI: <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/serverless-application-model/latest/developerguide/install-sam-cli.html\">https://docs.aws.amazon.com/serverless-application-model/latest/developerguide/install-sam-cli.html</a></li>\n<li>Install the VSCode AWS Toolkit plugin</li>\n<li>Log in to AWS through the VSCode AWS Toolkit</li>\n<li>Right-click on the Lambda section and select Create Lambda SAM Application</li>\n<li>Write your code inside the <code class=\"language-text\">lambda_handler</code> function</li>\n<li>Build: Add required packages to requirements and build the image using the <code class=\"language-text\">sam build</code> command. If no package installation is needed, the <code class=\"language-text\">--skip-pull-image</code> option can be used to skip the image pull. Running <code class=\"language-text\">sam build</code> creates the <code class=\"language-text\">.aws-sam</code> folder.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sam build (--skip-pull-image)</code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"7\">\n<li>Test (invoke): After writing a sample event in <code class=\"language-text\">event.json</code>, you can test the local Lambda function. The function must be rebuilt before testing to apply any changes. Using the <code class=\"language-text\">sam local start-api</code> command launches a server at <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:3000\">http://127.0.0.1:3000</a>, enabling debugging via Postman.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sam local invoke -e events/event.json\n\n# If you have an error when finding docker, run command below\nDOCKER_HOST=unix://$HOME/.docker/run/docker.sock sam local invoke -e events/event.json</code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 760px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/4fa52/24-06-21-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 12.105263157894738%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAACCAYAAABYBvyLAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEwEAmpwYAAAAf0lEQVR42i3NWw6CMABEUZYBbQRaoS81ApEYIGqRxP3v6NqgHyczmZ/JxnFkmRemaabvB7puIJzOhBAwrUEpjdZHDmWJECKR//x1KSVFUZDn+Z5ZjJHXI7I+t+S929YP99vE9dJjGodtPLb1NLrFGof3HufSbu2urut0rKiqii+dQjs4RlvWQQAAAABJRU5ErkJggg=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/15813/24-06-21-1.webp 190w,\n/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/1cdb2/24-06-21-1.webp 380w,\n/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/9046c/24-06-21-1.webp 760w,\n/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/c89f9/24-06-21-1.webp 1140w,\n/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/67580/24-06-21-1.webp 1241w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/a2d4f/24-06-21-1.png 190w,\n/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/3f520/24-06-21-1.png 380w,\n/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/3c051/24-06-21-1.png 760w,\n/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/b5cea/24-06-21-1.png 1140w,\n/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/4fa52/24-06-21-1.png 1241w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/ae00b8ea25531f3256d69723b0c3b50c/3c051/24-06-21-1.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ol start=\"8\">\n<li>Deployment: Deployment settings can be configured in the <code class=\"language-text\">template.yaml</code> file.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sam deploy # Add --guided option for first-time deployment</code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"9\">\n<li>Test events for Lambda can be referenced from <a href=\"https://github.com/aws/aws-lambda-go/tree/main/events/testdata\">this repository</a>.</li>\n<li>Role configuration is required. Refer to <a href=\"https://devblog.kakaostyle.com/ko/2017-05-13-1-aws-serverless-1/\">Kakao Style's tech blog</a>.\n<ul>\n<li>SQS-related required permissions: <code class=\"language-text\">sqs:ReceiveMessage</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">sqs:DeleteMessage</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">sqs:GetQueueAttributes</code></li>\n<li>Lambda-related required permissions: <code class=\"language-text\">lambda:InvokeFunction</code></li>\n<li>CloudWatch-related required permissions: <code class=\"language-text\">logs:CreateLogGroup</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">logs:CreateLogStream</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">logs:PutLogEvents</code></li>\n<li>If S3 access is needed, assign a role such as AmazonS3FullAccess</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"slack-webhook-bot\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#slack-webhook-bot\" aria-label=\"slack webhook bot permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Slack Webhook Bot</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a Slack App, then enable 'Activate Incoming Webhooks' in the 'Incoming Webhooks' section.\n<ul>\n<li>What is a WebHook?: <a href=\"https://docs.tosspayments.com/resources/glossary/webhook\">https://docs.tosspayments.com/resources/glossary/webhook</a></li>\n<li>Unlike a client calling a server, the server calls the client when a specific event occurs, which is why it is also called a 'reverse API.'</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>In the 'Incoming Webhooks' section, add the channel to use the webhook via 'Add New Webhook to Workspace.'</li>\n<li>Check and copy the generated Webhook URL.</li>\n<li>Test that it works correctly via curl. Then use the Webhook URL within the Lambda function.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">curl -s -d \"payload={'text':'hello world'}\" \"YOUR_WEBHOOK_URL\"</code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 627px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d6e32375f7cdb1f458970aed6f346527/e9c9b/24-06-21-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.78947368421053%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/d6e32375f7cdb1f458970aed6f346527/15813/24-06-21-2.webp 190w,\n/static/d6e32375f7cdb1f458970aed6f346527/1cdb2/24-06-21-2.webp 380w,\n/static/d6e32375f7cdb1f458970aed6f346527/c4111/24-06-21-2.webp 627w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 627px) 100vw, 627px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/d6e32375f7cdb1f458970aed6f346527/a2d4f/24-06-21-2.png 190w,\n/static/d6e32375f7cdb1f458970aed6f346527/3f520/24-06-21-2.png 380w,\n/static/d6e32375f7cdb1f458970aed6f346527/e9c9b/24-06-21-2.png 627w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 627px) 100vw, 627px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/d6e32375f7cdb1f458970aed6f346527/e9c9b/24-06-21-2.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"aws-simple-queue-service-sqs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#aws-simple-queue-service-sqs\" aria-label=\"aws simple queue service sqs permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>AWS Simple Queue Service (SQS)</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Create an AWS SQS queue and configure the access policy.\n<ul>\n<li>A common pattern is to set up an SNS notification on a specific service (e.g., S3) and have the SQS queue subscribe to that SNS topic.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Set the Lambda function created above as the Lambda trigger for the SQS queue.</li>\n<li>Save and verify the results.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 760px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/53639/24-06-21-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 29.47368421052632%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/15813/24-06-21-3.webp 190w,\n/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/1cdb2/24-06-21-3.webp 380w,\n/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/9046c/24-06-21-3.webp 760w,\n/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/c89f9/24-06-21-3.webp 1140w,\n/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/6ae26/24-06-21-3.webp 1358w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/a2d4f/24-06-21-3.png 190w,\n/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/3f520/24-06-21-3.png 380w,\n/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/3c051/24-06-21-3.png 760w,\n/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/b5cea/24-06-21-3.png 1140w,\n/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/53639/24-06-21-3.png 1358w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/d3f933c4d61ce2217b2cdd1e7a9c34e6/3c051/24-06-21-3.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>If you want to inspect messages directly, go to 'Send and receive messages' in the SQS console, poll for messages, and check the results.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"summary\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#summary\" aria-label=\"summary permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Summary</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>A specific event occurs (e.g., SNS)</li>\n<li>The event is delivered to Lambda via SQS</li>\n<li>The lambda_handler in Lambda checks whether an alert is needed for the event</li>\n<li>If an alert is needed, a message is sent to the Slack webhook URL</li>\n<li>The alert is confirmed in the Slack channel</li>\n</ol>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#aws-serverless-application-model-sam\">AWS Serverless Application Model (SAM)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#slack-webhook-bot\">Slack Webhook Bot</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#aws-simple-queue-service-sqs\">AWS Simple Queue Service (SQS)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#summary\">Summary</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/Operations/24-06-22/","title":"Alert System with SQS, Lambda, and Slack","category":"Operations","date":"2024-06-22"}}},"pageContext":{"postPath":"/Operations/24-06-22/","language":"eng","langRegex":"/contents/eng/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2145088972","256249292","63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}